			<P align="left">1.&nbsp;&nbsp; North Shore Channel: Lake Michigan to North Side WRP<BR>
				2.&nbsp;&nbsp; North Shore Channel: North Side WRP to the confluence with the 
				North Branch of the Chicago River (NBCR)<BR>
				3.&nbsp;&nbsp; NBCR: confluence with the North Shore Channel to Wolf Point, 
				including the North Branch Canal east of Goose Island.<BR>
				4.&nbsp;&nbsp; NBCR: Beckwith Road and West Fork to confluence with the North 
				Shore Channel<BR>
				5.&nbsp;&nbsp; Chicago River: Wolf Point to Chicago River Controlling Works 
				(CRCW)<BR>
				6.&nbsp;&nbsp; South Branch of Chicago River: Wolf Point to Damen Avenue<BR>
				7.&nbsp;&nbsp; South Fork of SBCR (Bubbly Creek)<BR>
				8.&nbsp;&nbsp; Chicago Sanitary and Ship Canal (CSSC): Damen Avenue to the 
				Stickney WRP<BR>
				9.&nbsp;&nbsp; CSSC: Stickney WRP to the confluence with the Calumet-Sag 
				Channel<BR>
				10. CSSC: from the confluence with the Calumet-Sag Channel to the Lemont WRP<BR>
				11. CSSC: Lemont WRP to Lockport Lock &amp; Dam<BR>
				12. Weller Creek<BR>
				13. Des Plaines River: Weller Creek to Willow-Higgins Creek<BR>
				14. Des Plaines River: Willow-Higgins Creek to the confluence with Salt Creek<BR>
				15. Des Plaines River: the confluence with Salt Creek to the confluence with 
				the CSSC<BR>
				16. Salt Creek: from Addison Creek to the confluence with the Des Plaines River<BR>
				17. Calumet River: O'Brien Locks to Lake Michigan<BR>
				18. Grand Calumet River: from confluence with the Little Calumet River to the 
				Indiana state line<BR>
				19. Little Calumet River: O'Brien Locks to the Calumet-Sag Channel<BR>
